The problem of Manual, back-and-forth appointment scheduling through phone, email, or paper calendars affects small service providers, such as photographers, barbers, and tutors. The impact of which is wasted time, double-booking, and frustrated clients that hurt revenue, efficiency, and reputation.

For small, appointment-driven businesses who currently coordinate bookings by hand. Planit is a web application for centralizing availability into a shareable link and lets clients self-schedule, unlike a general-purpose tool like Google Calendar. Our product prevents conflicts with real-time availability checks, sends automated reminders, supports priority-ranked time slots, has a fast and simple UI for speedy, low-stakes signup times, and instantly syncs all available, booked, and edited time blocks with Google Calendar for personal calendar integration.






**Value Proposition:** 

Reduces manual scheduling time by up to 90% and prevents double-bookings for solo and micro-team service providers by giving them a centralized, shareable booking calendar with automated reminders.

**Customer Segment:** 

Solo and small-team appointment-driven service providers, such as photographers, estheticians, tutors, and small non-profit coordinators, who currently spend 30 to 90 minutes weekly managing multiple bookings via phone, email, or paper, and need a reliable self-service scheduling link with real-time notifications.

**Stakeholders:**

Small Business Owners – These are the primary users that the product will be built for. They will define and update their availability blocks, share the booking link with clients, review and cancel bookings when needed.

Clients and Attendees – These are the people that will use the application to sign up for available time blocks. They will select a time block, enter their name, email, and phone number to reserve the booking and receive confirmation and reminder messages.

Development Team – This internal group of engineers, designers, and testers is responsible for building the working product. They will gather user feedback, design the system architecture and UI/UX flows, implement frontend and backend, write and maintain automated tests, and iterate on prototypes based on usability findings.

Competitive Scheduling Platforms – Well-established tools like Calendly, Google Calendar Appointment Slots, and Microsoft Bookings serve as the benchmarks. Analyzing their features, pricing models, and user workflows informs the differentiation strategy.








**Functional Requirements:**

1\. User Authentication and Profile Management

2\. Calendar Creation and Configuration

3\. Availability Block Management

4\. Shareable Booking Link Generator

5\. Client Self-Service Booking

6\. Booking Management Dashboard

7\. Automated Confirmation and Reminder Notification

8\. Booking Cancellation and Rescheduling

9\. Priority-Ranked Time Slots

10\. Multiple Event Types and Service Durations

11\. QR Code Generation for Booking Links

12\. Real-Time Availability Updates

13\. Usage Analytics and Reports

14\. Google Calendar Integration

**Nonfunctional Requirements:**


The system shall not require clients to create accounts but shall prevent unauthorized access to business owner dashboards through secure account authentication.


The system shall make sure that only authorized business owners can access and manage their booking information through secure authentication methods to protect sensitive booking information.

The System shall provide a responsive and intuitive user interface that loads within a few seconds on all forms of the application ensuring ease of use for all clients.

The web client shall function without errors or visual defects on the latest version of all major web browsers. Such as Chrome, Safari, Firefox, and Edge.

The login system shall use simple encryption to ensure the user’s data is secure.







**MVP:**

The MVP will deliver the core scheduling experience. It will need the following features implemented:

- Owner sign-up/login
  - Login Screen and User Validation
  - Data Persistence
- Availability block creation and insertion with priority levels
  - Render a calendar
  - UI for adding/editing/deleting time blocks
  - UI for configuring time blocks’ priority, notifications, and longevity
- Shareable public booking link (no client account required)
  - Link generator
  - QR code generator
- Client self-service booking
  - Client-side view of the calendar
  - Client signup and notification information collection

Example Usage of the MVP:

1. **1. Owner Onboarding**

   1\.1. Navigate to the app and choose to sign up with email/password or “Sign in 	with Google.”

   1\.2. Complete OAuth flow (if Google)

1. **Availability Setup**

   2\.1. After login, land on the “My Calendar” screen showing an interactive 			calendar grid.

   2\.2. Add a time block using a simple form.

   2\.3. Configure each block’s priority level, notification preferences, and how long 	it remains bookable.

1. **Link & QR Code Generation**

   3\.1. Click “Generate Link” to create a unique public URL for booking.

3\.2. (Optional) Click “Generate QR” to download a QR code for that URL.

1. **Client Booking**

   4\.1. Client opens the shared URL (or scans the QR code) and sees available slots 	in a read-only calendar view.

   4\.2. Client selects a slot, enters their name and email, and submits the booking 	form.

1. **Booking Confirmation & Sync**

   5\.1. App creates a booking record in the database.

   5\.2. Push the confirmed booking as an event into the owner’s Google Calendar 	with client details.

1. **Dashboard & Management**

   6\.1. Owner returns to their dashboard to see a list of upcoming bookings.

**User Stories:**
As a busy student I want to rebook a previous appointment with one tap, so that I can save time when scheduling recurring things like tutoring or study rooms.

As a student with a shifting schedule, I want instant notifications for high priority bookings, so that I don't miss important appointments even when I’m distracted or busy.


As a business owner, I want to see all upcoming bookings in a single calendar view so that I can stay organized and avoid double-booking.



As a client, I want to receive a confirmation and reminder notification after booking so that I don’t forget my appointment.

As a business owner, I want to control how far in advance clients can book or reschedule appointments so that I can manage my daily work schedule. 

As a client, I want to view available time slots and book my preferred service without needing to create an account, so that I can quickly schedule an appointment hassle free.


As a small business owner, I want to have an easy way to show my client my times of availability so that we can easily find a time that works for both of us.

As a client of a small service provider, I want to quickly see time slots that we will both be available for the services.

As a project manager I want to color code tasks so that I am able to divide multiple projects on the calendar.

As a video producer, I want to share an event on the calendar so that my actors can see the agenda for the video shoot.

As a project manager, I want to filter tasks by color on the calendar so that I can quickly view tasks for each project separately

As a video producer, I want to receive notification when someone views or comments on the shared calendar event so that I can ensure the team is prepared.
